# Gradle & Version Catalog

All dependency and plugin versions live in `gradle/libs.versions.toml`. **Never** hardcode versions in `build.gradle.kts`.

## Adding a dependency
1. Add the version to `[versions]` (only if it's a new line).
2. Declare the library in `[libraries]` using `version.ref`.
3. Reference it in `app/build.gradle.kts` via `libs.<alias>`.

```toml
# gradle/libs.versions.toml
[versions]
coil = "2.7.0"

[libraries]
coil-compose = { group = "io.coil-kt", name = "coil-compose", version.ref = "coil" }
```

```kotlin
// app/build.gradle.kts
dependencies {
    implementation(libs.coil.compose)
}
```

## Plugins
- Declare plugins in `[plugins]` of the catalog and apply via `alias(libs.plugins.<name>)`.
- Top-level `build.gradle.kts` uses `apply false`; modules apply directly.

## Compose BOM
- Compose artifacts must come through `platform(libs.androidx.compose.bom)`—do not pin individual Compose versions.

## SDK / Java
- Keep `minSdk = 24`, `targetSdk = 36`, `compileSdk { release(36) }`.
- Java/Kotlin source compatibility stays at **Java 11**. Do not bump without explicit request.

## Don't
- Don't introduce KAPT if KSP works (faster builds).
- Don't add `mavenLocal()` or extra repositories without need; existing config uses `google()` + `mavenCentral()`.
